SSyynnooppssiiss
       cc [options] file -lcurses #include <curses.h>

       int notimeout(WINDOW *win, bool bf);

       void timeout(int delay);

       void wtimeout(WINDOW *win, int delay);

DDeessccrriippttiioonn
       The  function specifies whether Timeout Mode or No Timeout
       Mode is in effect for the screen associated with the spec-
       ified  window.   If  bf  is TRUE, this screen is set to No
       Timeout Mode.  If bf is FALSE, this screen is set to Time-
       out Mode.  The initial state is FALSE.

       The  and  functions  set blocking or non-blocking read for
       the current or specified window  based  on  the  value  of
       delay:  One  or  more blocking reads (indefinite waits for
       input) are used.  One or more non-blocking reads are used.
       Any  Curses input function will fail if every character of
       the requested string is not  immediately  available.   Any
       Curses  input  function  blocks for delay milliseconds and
       fails if there is still no input.

RReettuurrnn vvaalluuee
       Upon successful completion, the function returns OK.  Oth-
       erwise, it returns ERR.

       The and functions do not return a value.

EErrrroorrss
       No errors are defined.

